Global Express Authorized Locations

Washington Gas has partnered with Global Express Financial Services ("Global Express") to provide authorized payment locations for customers to pay their natural gas bills.
As the authorized walk-in payment provider for Washington Gas, Global Express will accept cash-only payments for Washington Gas bills at more than 300 authorized payment locations in Washington, D.C., Maryland and Virginia. Global Express will accept payments for both residential and commercial natural gas accounts.
For your convenience, 13 of these locations are "fee free," including four in Washington, D.C., four in Maryland and five in Virginia. Only at these “fee free” locations will customers not be charged a convenience fee to make cash payments on their Washington Gas account.
View a list of “fee free” payment locations.
Global Express is the only authorized walk-in payment provider for Washington Gas. When making a payment, the customer should ask the agent to use the Global Express system to take their Washington Gas payment. Washington Gas can only verify walk-in payments made through the Global Express system. Payments made through other walk-in payment services cannot be verified in real-time.
Customers making payments at authorized payment locations other than the 13 "fee free" locations will be charged a convenience fee of $1.50 per transaction. This fee is paid directly to Global Express and must be paid in cash at the time of the transaction. No portion of this fee is shared with Washington Gas.
Search for a Global Express Payment Location near you.
Customers who are subject to disconnection or require re-connection must call the Washington Gas Customer Service line at 703-750-1000. The customer must provide the payment authorization number, their service address and account number to a Customer Service representative. The representative will verify payment and can either stop service termination for the next business day or place a re-connection order. Payments received between 2:00 p.m. the prior day and 2:00 p.m. on the current day will be credited the same business day. Payments made after 2:00 p.m. will be posted the next business day (excluding weekends and holidays).
For additional Global Express payment locations, call 800-989-6669.
You may pay your gas bill through the Quick Collect service at Western Union locations nationwide. Call Western Union at 800-325-6000 or visit their website for the location nearest you and for applicable Western Union service fees.















