                                                                        How do these fees work?


                                                                           Chat with our experts to find out more




                                                                     Things you need to know:

                                                                     One year service agreement required. Please note, if you decide not to choose a new service plan, you will be renewed under your current plan at the price in place at the time of your renewal. Price includes generation and transmission, but does not include utility distribution, taxes or other utility charges. Other taxes and fees may apply. Price is not regulated by the Commission. XOOM's charges will be reflected on the monthly bill you receive from Washington Gas and Light. If you cancel your service before the contract ends, a cost recovery fee of $110 may apply. If you are currently under a contract with another provider understand your obligations and rights before switching. Only the utility account holder or persons legally authorized on the account may enroll.*This promotion is sponsored by XOOM Energy, LLC (XOOM Energy), including its wholly owned subsidiaries, doing business at 11208 Statesville Road, Suite 200, Huntersville, North Carolina 28078.  The proceeds from the promotion will benefit PetSmart Charities, Inc. (“Charities”).  XOOM Energy will pay to Charities in the US for its general charitable purposes the equivalent of 5% of monthly energy charges paid by participating XOOM Energy customers who enroll from December 1, 2016 through November 30, 2017. This contribution is not tax deductible.  Charities is an organization described in Internal Revenue Code Section 501(c)(3).  A copy of its most recent financial report is available by contacting the organization at 19601 North 27th Ave., Phoenix, AZ 85027, or by telephone at 1-800-423-7387. For more information, visit www.petsmartcharities.org. Registration by Charities or the Promoter with any state regulatory agency does not imply endorsement.




















