        7/12/2017
    

Since no one in customer service seems to be listening to me I have had to go to social media to see if I can get help. I have been waiting over two months to get gas installed in my house. I am converting my oven, water heater and fireplace. I am waiting at my house for the fourth time for someone to install the meter. First and second time no one showed up. Third time they showed up but I need to Airflow to add a piece of equipment. This has been installed so I called and setup an appointment. I called Washington Gas yesterday and got confirmation someone was coming today and I called this morning and they confirmed again. I am now on the phone and have been told that they are not coming. Four days out of work and my window was 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. Now my husband will have to be at the house on Friday from 7 a.m. to 5 p.m. This is ridiculous. If there was another gas company I could use I would be out of here. Someone high up needs to know that there is no communication with customers, customer service, dispatch and contractors. This is only the tip of the iceberg of what I have been through.




