        1/26/2017
    

I hardly ever write reviews but was compelled to add my warnings to the many others about Washington Gas.METICULOUSLY REVIEW YOUR BILLS!  After my first bill their auto-pay system failed to draft my bank account for the second and subsequent bills.  Since I have never experienced issues before in 17 years of using auto-pay for utilities, I didn't look at the bills posted on my Washington Gas account online.  It wasn't until Washington Gas physically mailed me a disconnect warning that I signed into my account to see what was going on and saw that auto-draft was not working.  My mistake for not assuming they might be incompetent.  Then they added a $65 deposit charge to my next bill since my payment had been considered "late" even though the lateness was due to their auto-pay system failure.  Fine, whatever.Thereafter, I opted out of auto-pay and manually paid each bill online each month.  Interestingly, the first payment manually made online was reflected in the account payment history and the next bill as expected; but subsequent payments for subsequent bills were not credited to the bills even though they are listed in the account payment history.  They took my money but never credited my account. I called Customer Service for an explanation; the representative agreed that she saw the payments but I wasn't getting credited in the bills.  She forwarded the matter to the billing department where they should investigate the issue and have a resolution in 14 days.  I asked why doesn't she just transfer me to that department while I was on the phone so we could resolve it immediately and she responded that they have to follow a process, which takes two weeks to complete.  Wow.I am moving out of the country in about a week so I imagine that it will be a source of unneeded frustration to collect the $65 deposit and get a resolution to their billing issues while I'm overseas.I'll leave you with one positive; the Customer Service representatives are courteous and professional despite working with a problematic computer system.  When scheduling a stop date for my service, it literally took the representative over five minutes before she could access my account and over 10 minutes more just to setup the stop service date and forwarding address.  They must be using Tandy computers leftover from 1984 with 300 baud modems to connect to the internet!




