I want to thank the man from your company at 13504 Hillendale Dr. Woodbridge, Va. I didn't get his name but I was so pleased with his service at my home. He took his time to investigated why I smelled gas. Found the problem and it ended up with a easy fix from a month ago. He listened to what I had back then and found my problem that otherwise he would have to shut my gas off. He took care of it simple fix. I am asking to have him commended for his time and his patience. Thank you.







Much to my surprise, the late night Washington Gas customer service is fantastic.  I called Washington Gas at 9:05 pm to report a non-emergency problem and a technician came to my house and completely resolved the issue by 11:30 pm.  Both the technician and phone operator were shockingly competent and nice.  The technician even voluntarily helped change my a/c filter.







Their website may just well be the worst on the internet.  My guess is it was designed in 1997.  Its slow, and the bill pay service is archaic. Good luck getting anything of substance from the site.  I have signed up for auto-pay and budget billing multiple times but it never goes into effect.  In addition, I schedule payments and they don't show on the website (although I receive emails stating the payment has been scheduled).  

But with that said, I have had no problems with their service, hence the 2 stars.







The physical washington gas location has very pleasant employees, I even had to call the emergency line once because of my carbon monoxide alarms going off. Despite it being around 2 am they had someone at my house in about 20 minutes to check everything. As far as paying bills or getting ahold of someone on the phone it would be hard to give this company even 2 stars, everything is outsouced to the Philippines I believe. The bill pay area of Their website is a mess, its so bad now I just go pay my bill at their office despite the inconvenience.







HORRIBLE experience with their phone customer service on multiple instances.  The only reason I am giving two stars is because when I HAD to go to a center in person, the woman there was helpful and apologetic.  I was trying to start service from out of state and my apartment complex was very clear that I couldn't get the keys until I gave them utility account numbers.  I spent at least an hour and a half on hold total during all of my calls, they couldn't transfer service over the phone and asked me if I lived in Vermont (I was moving from RI to VA), told me to fax or email two forms of ID and my lease agreement (which I did), and after speaking to numerous people, I was told I had to set it up in person.  I lived 7 hours away!  Luckily, my complex worked with me and I went after I had moved in.  As I said, the woman who helped me was able to set up my account in MINUTES and had no idea why they wouldn't do it over the phone, apologizing to me.  And THEN, two weeks later, I get a letter in the mail saying that they received my email with my lease agreement but need two forms of ID, had mis-typed my email address, AND clearly, I already have service.  I don't think I've ever dealt with such incompetent customer service.  Hopefully I won't have to deal with them again until I move out!







This service via the phone is absolutely horrible. I am a new customer and they gave me a 5 hour window for the time to wait. A little long but I requested they come first thing in the morning. I have done this with every other utility company and they usually come earlier in the morning rather than later. They said I would receive a confirmation call. No confirmation call the day before so I called to confirm. There are still nothing in the notes as requested to ask the technician to come earlier in the morning. I request them to add it in the notes again. Well the morning is progressing so I call to see if they are still coming. Even though I called in twice, there is still nothing in the notes and they cannot call the technician to verify because guess what, they are in the Phillipines. I have to spell out every single word because their first language is not English. Seriously! This is an excellent reason why they should not outsource jobs to foreign countries. Washington gas you need to bring the call center back to the U.S. so customers dont need to call in 50 times to attempt to get a question answered. It is a shame that washington gas is a monopoly.

The only reason they get two stars is because the technican was very professional and did the job quickly. I didnt feel the slightest bit uncomfortable with him as a female in the home alone. If I was reviewing the technician at the home, it would be a 5. But, I will likely interact an idiotic customer service much more than the technician.







