        5/13/2017
    

Not sure I have a single positive thing to say about this business. It's frustrating that there aren't any other options. When I moved into my apartment, the former landlord (who is also a moron) told me my gas was taken care of. Trusting him, I never tried to sign up for an account. The gas was working just fine and continued to work for the next year and two months. One day, I notice it stops working so I call the landlord (at this point, it's a new landlord). He calls the gas company, and they tell me that it's been turned off because no one has paid the bill. What? They say I need to call so I do. I get this completely rude and ignorant person on the phone, who tells me it's my fault and that I was "naive" to think I could just get free gas. I tell her, no, my landlord told me it was included but that also if it hadn't been paid they should have sent notice. She said they don't send notices, as it's the customers responsibility to know when they haven't paid a bill. I ask her why after FIFTEEN months of unpaid service, they wouldn't notify a single person. She begins to get angry and say it's my fault, basically tells me I don't understand how utility payments work, and that I have to pay an outstanding balance of $370 in order to regain service. She also told me I would have to bring a copy of my lease to the office in DC in order to pay these bills. I tell her I don't really have time do to all that and she says that's my problem, too bad. After talking to several different people, I finally managed to get a very sweet woman on the phone, who said the other woman was only trying to make things hard for me. I eventually had the situation resolved with this nice woman, but holy crap. This company knows it has you trapped so it doesn't care if it provides horrible service.




