        6/5/2017
    

Washington Gas is the worst utility company EVER! In anticipation for a May 30th move to Hyattsville, MD, I called on May 15 to have the gas turned on and placed n my name. When I moved in on the 30th, there was no Gas Service. I called and they said there was perhaps an issue with the gas line. They scheduled a technician to arrive some time on Friday, June 2nd. Mind you, they can't give you an ETA or time of day for the technician, so you have to be home all day. This doesn't work out if you have a job that doesn't allow you to take off with short notice. I called the morning of June 2nd to confirm the appointment. The customer service rep said it looked like I had no contract! So she set up a contract and then confirmed that a tech would be out to service the line. I waited all day and the tech was a NO SHOW! I called first thing Monday (today) and the rep said they had too many emergency calls to get to my order on Friday. She promised someone would be out today. The tech showed up about an hour later, however he was ACROSS THE STREET! I had to wave him down. He came by and asked my name. According to his tablet, my name was placed on the account for the vacant house across the street. And he told me he couldn't service my gas line because the order was made for the other house and its meter number. So I had to call the Washington Gas AGAIN to walk them through the process of associating my name with the correct address. Thankfully the rep I worked with was willing to take things slow, confirm the information, and had it reviewed by her manager. Although she said it could take up to 3 days to get someone out, she promised someone would be out today. My fingers are crossed. Washington Gas, shame on you for treating your customers like they don't matter because of the monopoly you have on the D.C. Area!!!!




