        3/13/2017
    

If it was possible to get zero stars that would be my preference.  It is currently below freezing in DC, just moved here and setting up service. The apt I am renting has no heat or hot water turned on when I moved in, which is normal. I have asthma (haven't had an attack in years) that is triggered by the cold and have already used by breathing machine 2x this weekend and had to get a hotel sunday night.  I had a service window from 7am-5pm Monday. The guy called at 3:15 and said he was on his way. Called the gas company at 5pm and he was pulled onto another job... they weren't going to call or reschedule.  I asked them to please come out, my asthma was really bad from being in the cold apt all day and I was having serious trouble breathing at this point, and having difficulty even getting my words out to the technician.  I called 8x (8x) to express that I am in an emergency situation, have no where to go in a new city and can't afford another hotel bc they cannot honor their commitment... I put my health in jeopardy to honor the time slot they provided but they didn't seem to care. I was told over and over again... this is not an emergency for them and if I want to go to the hospital that is my choice.  My husband then called and pleaded for the supervisor to have some sympathy for an asthmatic that is having an attack bc they didn't honor their commitment.  They said a technician would be here by midnight. I just received another call (it's 11pm)... they are hoping someone will get here by 1am!!!  So let just pretend they will show up tonight, I would have been waiting here for 18 hours. I am currently attached to my breathing machine, which I haven't used in years. The people at Washington gas have no humanity.  One woman I spoke to told me her son has asthma and she knows how scary and painful an attack is... but she still can't help me. If I were you, I would expect the least from this company and then you may end up having a satisfactory experience.




