        5/9/2017
    

Yelp needs a negative star rating... Washington Gas customer support people are utterly useless.  Both from calling their support number and e-mailing customersupport@washgas.….  Took me over a month to finally resolve a billing issue, where the home builder's bill was on my account.  Over the course of a month, I spoke with several customer support reps and maybe one or two were truly helpful. E-mailing customersupport@washgas.… is even worse. All they do is copy and paste pre-written bullshit and then write some bullshit saying your clarification request is still being processed. Nothing I received by e-mail was ever helpful. So pretty much their customer support is useless, cause they have a back office that actually solves the issues. It would seem like issues get lost in translation from customer support to their back office. The problem was that someone on the Wash Gas end screwed up when I called before closing to have the account transfer to my name on my requested effective date, which caused the builder's bill to show up in my account. Whatever, finally got it resolved. Try to hire some smarter people for your customer support.




